OL,3,CHow buy now pay later schemes are
OL,4,Cpushing families into debt
OL,6,F"You never know - you might even reach
OL,7,Fthe point where someone knocks on your
OL,8,Fdoor because you owe money to
OL,9,Fsomebody."
OL,11,FJaquilina is now on a repayment plan
OL,12,Fwith debt advice organisation Money
OL,13,FWellness and hopes to be debt-free
OL,14,Fwithin two years - but she is not the
OL,15,Fonly one who has got into trouble with
OL,16,Fthis sort of debt.
OL,18,FAccording to Blackhawk Network, just
OL,19,Funder half of UK consumers plan to use
OL,20,FBNPL to fund some of their Christmas
OL,21,Fspending.
