OL,3,CHow buy now pay later schemes are
OL,4,Cpushing families into debt
OL,6,FDebt advice charities say they are
OL,7,Fseeing a sharp rise in people
OL,8,Fstruggling to keep up with BNPL
OL,9,Frepayments.
OL,11,FMoney Wellness says 60% of customers
OL,12,Fwho contact them about BNPL debts are
OL,13,Fclassed as vulnerable, including
OL,14,Fpeople with health conditions or
OL,15,Fdisabilities.
OL,17,FMore than half also have arrears on
OL,18,Fpriority bills, such as council tax,
OL,19,Fgas, electricity or water.
